{
  "seo_keywords": ["Nimbus breach", "data leak", "customer data exposure", "security vulnerability", "engineering failure"]
}

{
  "draft_text": "Nimbus Announces Catastrophic Data Breach\n\nIn a shocking turn of events, Nimbus suffered a massive data breach on September 1st, 2023, exposing thousands of customers' emails and credit‑card numbers. Our internal investigation confirms that the breach was caused by a critical vulnerability in our back‑end API, which our engineering team failed to patch despite multiple warnings. This negligence has led to widespread media coverage and severe user backlash. Nimbus is currently working to mitigate the damage and will be conducting a full security overhaul."
}

{
  "proofread_text": "Nimbus Announces Catastrophic Data Breach\n\nIn a shocking turn of events, Nimbus suffered a massive data breach on September 1st, 2023, exposing thousands of customers' emails and credit‑card numbers. Our internal investigation confirms that the breach was caused by a critical vulnerability in our back‑end API, which our engineering team failed to patch despite multiple warnings. This negligence has led to widespread media coverage and severe user backlash. Nimbus is currently working to mitigate the damage and will be conducting a full security overhaul."
}

{
  "formatted_release": "<h1>Nimbus Announces Catastrophic Data Breach</h1><p>In a shocking turn of events, Nimbus suffered a massive data breach on September 1st, 2023, exposing thousands of customers' emails and credit‑card numbers. Our internal investigation confirms that the breach was caused by a critical vulnerability in our back‑end API, which our engineering team failed to patch despite multiple warnings. This negligence has led to widespread media coverage and severe user backlash. Nimbus is currently working to mitigate the damage and will be conducting a full security overhaul.</p>"
}
